UnitsDefinition.Comment:
Considerable confusion exists about the meanings of the SI (or metric) prefixes used with the unit byte, especially concerning the prefixes kilo (k or K), mega (M), and giga (G). Out bytes unit will consider the more common use of bytes and it's multiples, k, M, G.
To avoid confusion with already existing unti 'B' (level of power intensity) we will use Bytes as the unit name
